I ran a hormone panel on eddie.

265
00:15:17,835 --> 00:15:19,136
His prolactin's above normal.

266
00:15:19,204 --> 00:15:22,973
Means he's actually improving.

267
00:15:23,040 --> 00:15:25,609
Body chemistry changes
for all sorts of reasons...

268
00:15:25,676 --> 00:15:27,377
stress, fear... why not love?

269
00:15:27,445 --> 00:15:29,580
But maybe he's going into
some sort of remission.

270
00:15:29,647 --> 00:15:31,915
You haven't asked if i
learned anything relevant

271
00:15:31,983 --> 00:15:33,317
from the kutners.

272
00:15:33,384 --> 00:15:35,619
If you had, i'm sure
you'd have mentioned it.

273
00:15:35,686 --> 00:15:38,188
Or you're just afraid
there is something relevant.

274
00:15:38,256 --> 00:15:39,856
Which would mean you
could have saved him.

275
00:15:39,924 --> 00:15:43,059
I don't buy that suicide
is always a cry for help.

276
00:15:43,128 --> 00:15:46,296
Sometimes you just don't want help.

277
00:15:46,364 --> 00:15:49,566
Good thing you got some...

278
00:15:49,634 --> 00:15:54,704
or you'd have tried
again and gotten it right.

279
00:15:54,772 --> 00:15:57,674
She doesn't have wegener's.

280
00:15:57,742 --> 00:16:01,378
Kidney function's normal.
It's not byssinosis.

281
00:16:01,446 --> 00:16:04,981
It's not mitral valve
stenosis. Nothing fits.

282
00:16:05,049 --> 00:16:08,218
If it doesn't fit any diagnosis...

283
00:16:08,286 --> 00:16:11,655
it just leaves one diagnosis.

284
00:16:15,460 --> 00:16:17,794
I'm dr. House.

285
00:16:17,862 --> 00:16:19,429
You have hypertrophic cardiomyopathy.

286
00:16:19,497 --> 00:16:21,731
His heart is too weak.
Yours is too strong.

287
00:16:21,799 --> 00:16:23,300
Good news is it's fixable.

288
00:16:23,368 --> 00:16:25,001
We induce a massive heart attack

289
00:16:25,069 --> 00:16:26,470
and kill off the extra muscle.

290
00:16:26,538 --> 00:16:27,937
You wanna give me a heart attack?

291
00:16:28,005 --> 00:16:30,340
It's only dangerous if
your heart is normal size.

292
00:16:30,408 --> 00:16:33,143
But since all the... are you serious?

293
00:16:33,211 --> 00:16:35,011
No.

294
00:16:35,079 --> 00:16:36,880
This is actually very annoying,

295
00:16:36,947 --> 00:16:38,815
and i'm getting really
bored of lying to patients

296
00:16:38,883 --> 00:16:40,116
to scare them into telling me the truth.

297
00:16:40,185 --> 00:16:41,718
She's faking.

298
00:16:41,786 --> 00:16:44,054
And yes, if she keeps faking,

299
00:16:44,121 --> 00:16:46,723
i'm going to eventually do
something that will kill her.

300
00:16:46,791 --> 00:16:49,092
How could she be... the windpipe thing?

301
00:16:49,160 --> 00:16:51,161
That was real. Treatment
made her better.

302
00:16:51,229 --> 00:16:52,696
But good for her was bad for you,

303
00:16:52,763 --> 00:16:54,998
which was bad for her,
so she made herself bad.

304
00:16:55,066 --> 00:16:56,500
It's all so simple.

305
00:16:56,568 --> 00:17:01,438
She figured the sicker she
was, the longer you'd hang on.

306
00:17:01,506 --> 00:17:03,807
Charlotte?

307
00:17:08,546 --> 00:17:11,014
We haven't been this close for years.

308
00:17:11,082 --> 00:17:13,717
I wanted to hang on to that.

309
00:17:15,386 --> 00:17:18,655
Oh, please. People hate reruns.

310
00:17:18,723 --> 00:17:20,857
It's my leg. I swear this is real!

311
00:17:20,925 --> 00:17:23,026
What, you pinky swear,
or you just plain swear?

312
00:17:23,094 --> 00:17:24,428
Because...

313
00:17:24,495 --> 00:17:29,633
how can she fake that?

314
00:17:29,701 --> 00:17:32,736
She can't.

315
00:17:34,575 --> 00:17:36,943
so...what can shred an epiglottis

316
00:17:37,010 --> 00:17:38,878
and make muscle disappear?

317
00:17:38,946 --> 00:17:42,882
Mr. And mrs. Kutner.

318
00:17:42,950 --> 00:17:44,651
They caused kutner's
death. Why not charlotte's?

319
00:17:44,718 --> 00:17:46,419
Mourning period's over.

320
00:17:46,487 --> 00:17:48,054
Foreman's sense of irony is back.

321
00:17:48,121 --> 00:17:51,791
I was wrong about the ethnic reason.

322
00:17:51,859 --> 00:17:54,461
Step one... change your name back.

323
00:17:54,528 --> 00:17:56,529
Step two... if step one fails,

324
00:17:56,597 --> 00:17:58,965
move to bangalore.

325
00:17:59,032 --> 00:18:01,768
Step 14... if step 13
doesn't work, kill yourself.

326
00:18:01,836 --> 00:18:04,070
So what now... you gonna insult
your way through his rolodex

327
00:18:04,137 --> 00:18:05,572
till you find someone with an answer?

328
00:18:05,639 --> 00:18:07,406
I've been polite to
the friends i've called,

329
00:18:07,475 --> 00:18:09,976
all of whom were useless.
They weren't useless.

330
00:18:10,043 --> 00:18:12,479
They just didn't know
anything more than we did.

331
00:18:12,546 --> 00:18:14,013
Tomato, tomah-to.

332
00:18:14,081 --> 00:18:16,415
M.s. Weakens myelin sheath,
compromises nerve conduction.

333
00:18:16,484 --> 00:18:18,785
I'm talking about charlotte,
the one who's still alive.

334
00:18:18,853 --> 00:18:21,020
You two, stick her in an mri.

335
00:18:21,088 --> 00:18:23,322
Confirm m.s.

336
00:18:23,390 --> 00:18:24,657
And you run the echo on eddie

337
00:18:24,725 --> 00:18:26,593
that you're planning
to do behind my back

338
00:18:26,660 --> 00:18:29,428
to see if his heart's improving.

339
00:18:31,665 --> 00:18:33,733
Did you let me hire a pervert?

340
00:18:33,801 --> 00:18:36,102
Well, it would
hypocritical of me not to.

341
00:18:36,169 --> 00:18:39,171
Kutner's police background
check from when he started.

342
00:18:39,239 --> 00:18:41,307
He was charged with indecent exposure.

343
00:18:41,375 --> 00:18:43,643
Kutner streaked at the
penn-dartmouth football game.

344
00:18:43,711 --> 00:18:47,179
Precisely the kind of thing
you'd expect him to do.

345
00:18:47,247 --> 00:18:50,617
It's okay. You should be upset.

346
00:18:50,684 --> 00:18:53,386
He thought like you,
pushed boundaries like you.

347
00:18:53,453 --> 00:18:55,755
If he thought like me...

348
00:18:55,823 --> 00:18:57,456
he would have known
that living in misery

349
00:18:57,525 --> 00:19:01,260
sucks marginally less than dying in it.

350
00:19:03,797 --> 00:19:05,231
Just a few more minutes,

351
00:19:05,298 --> 00:19:08,267
then we'll get you back to eddie.

352
00:19:08,335 --> 00:19:10,336
What's it like, 30
years with the same man?

353
00:19:10,404 --> 00:19:13,105
Great for me.

354
00:19:13,173 --> 00:19:16,308
Good for him, i hope.

355
00:19:16,376 --> 00:19:18,144
You don't think he loves you?

356
00:19:18,211 --> 00:19:21,147
I think he always loved me in his way.

357
00:19:21,214 --> 00:19:24,116
Just not in the "spend
time with me or show emotion

358
00:19:24,184 --> 00:19:28,154
or any affection for me" sort of way.

359
00:19:28,221 --> 00:19:31,223
Why did you stay?

360
00:19:31,291 --> 00:19:34,193
I didn't need him to feel about me

361
00:19:34,261 --> 00:19:36,729
the way i did about him.

362
00:19:36,797 --> 00:19:39,632
Love...doesn't...

363
00:19:39,700 --> 00:19:42,569
charlotte?

364
00:19:46,740 --> 00:19:49,008
I've heard stories

365
00:19:49,076 --> 00:19:53,880
of cancer patients going
into spontaneous remission.

366
00:19:53,948 --> 00:19:56,148
You think this might
be that sort of thing?

367
00:19:56,216 --> 00:19:57,650
It's unlikely, but you never know.

368
00:19:57,718 --> 00:20:00,019
If i just had a little more time...

369
00:20:00,087 --> 00:20:03,656
be with charlotte, try
and do better by her.

370
00:20:03,724 --> 00:20:05,024
Yeah, maybe.

371
00:20:05,092 --> 00:20:07,526
You don't think i mean it.

372
00:20:07,595 --> 00:20:10,329
I think you mean it now.

373
00:20:10,397 --> 00:20:11,564
I think it's much easier to mean it

374
00:20:11,632 --> 00:20:13,633
than to do anything about it.

375
00:20:22,309 --> 00:20:24,310
Chamber walls are barely moving.

376
00:20:24,377 --> 00:20:26,846
I'm sorry.

377
00:20:41,028 --> 00:20:43,362
He needs a friend.

378
00:20:43,430 --> 00:20:47,266
I can't...deal with this and house.

379
00:20:47,334 --> 00:20:48,835
You need a friend too.

380
00:20:48,902 --> 00:20:50,970
You couldn't give a crap what i need.

381
00:20:51,038 --> 00:20:54,107
You just want someone
to take care of him.

382
00:20:59,713 --> 00:21:03,116
He told kutner's parents
it was their fault.

383
00:21:08,522 --> 00:21:11,858
Ruptured spleen. Means it's not m.s.

384
00:21:11,925 --> 00:21:13,793
What are you doing here?

385
00:21:13,861 --> 00:21:15,762
Waiting for you to fix her spleen

386
00:21:15,829 --> 00:21:17,630
so we can biopsy it for
rheumatoid arthritis.

387
00:21:17,698 --> 00:21:19,431
I'll do it. Go home.

388
00:21:19,499 --> 00:21:23,636
She's not your patient.
And kutner wasn't my friend.

389
00:21:23,704 --> 00:21:27,273
Kutner wanted to die. Charlotte doesn't.

390
00:21:27,340 --> 00:21:29,108
So in a contest for my
concern and interest,

391
00:21:29,176 --> 00:21:30,810
she wins.

392
00:21:30,878 --> 00:21:33,345
Okay, either you're
a cold-hearted bastard

393
00:21:33,413 --> 00:21:34,881
or you're too miserable to face it.

394
00:21:34,948 --> 00:21:37,150
Go home and cry.

395
00:21:37,217 --> 00:21:40,053
It's not rheumatoid
arthritis. Her liver's scarred.

396
00:21:40,120 --> 00:21:43,956
Whatever she's got, it's spreading.

397
00:22:01,075 --> 00:22:03,009
For the record,

398
00:22:03,077 --> 00:22:07,814
i'm uncomfortable violating
a dead colleague's dignity.

399
00:22:10,884 --> 00:22:15,688
It's only violating it
if you find something.

400
00:22:15,756 --> 00:22:18,758
Good to see you.

401
00:22:18,826 --> 00:22:22,461
What are we looking for?

402
00:22:22,529 --> 00:22:24,997
He was hiding.

403
00:22:25,065 --> 00:22:26,298
Why?

404
00:22:26,366 --> 00:22:29,769
Shame? Fear?

405
00:22:29,837 --> 00:22:32,338
Are you okay?

406
00:22:32,405 --> 00:22:35,241
It's okay not to be okay.

407
00:22:35,308 --> 00:22:40,646
"Colonial warrior
blaster. Number one one."

408
00:22:40,714 --> 00:22:43,449
He'd have spent months
tracking this down.

409
00:22:43,516 --> 00:22:45,218
He had passions.

410
00:22:45,285 --> 00:22:48,420
He was obviously in pain.

411
00:22:48,488 --> 00:22:53,392
Does it really matter why?

412
00:22:53,460 --> 00:22:56,028
He hung the bad with the good.

413
00:22:56,096 --> 00:23:00,466
His loss beside a reminder
of what he'd gained.

414
00:23:00,533 --> 00:23:04,603
Means he was open about the pain.

415
00:23:04,671 --> 00:23:06,305
Should mean that if it got worse,

416
00:23:06,373 --> 00:23:08,540
he had no reason to hide it.

417
00:23:11,779 --> 00:23:14,113
Here's how we're gonna
handle this, house.

418
00:23:14,181 --> 00:23:17,183
We're gonna leave here
and go to the closest bar

419
00:23:17,251 --> 00:23:19,385
and drink and tell stories

420
00:23:19,452 --> 00:23:23,055
about the time kutner
almost blew up an o.r.

421
00:23:23,123 --> 00:23:26,159
And pass out in our own sick.

422
00:23:26,226 --> 00:23:29,461
Sound like a plan?

423
00:23:48,916 --> 00:23:52,952
What am i missing?

424
00:23:56,690 --> 00:23:59,525
You've got that look.

425
00:23:59,592 --> 00:24:01,294
You figured this out.

426
00:24:03,763 --> 00:24:06,032
You're not here because
you care about kutner.

427
00:24:06,099 --> 00:24:07,934
You're here because it's a mystery.

428
00:24:08,001 --> 00:24:11,437
You're here for the puzzle.

429
00:24:11,504 --> 00:24:13,306
What if i didn't miss anything...

430
00:24:13,373 --> 00:24:18,510
'cause there's nothing to miss?

431
00:24:18,578 --> 00:24:21,848
He didn't kill himself.

432
00:24:21,915 --> 00:24:24,917
He was murdered.

433
00:24:43,747 --> 00:24:45,549
Epiglottis muscle,
spleen, and now her liver,

434
00:24:45,616 --> 00:24:48,818
which is operating at 20%
and deteriorating fast.

435
00:24:48,886 --> 00:24:51,588
Autoimmune hepatitis?
Did you page foreman?

436
00:24:51,655 --> 00:24:54,057
Took up cuddy's offer of time off.

437
00:24:54,125 --> 00:24:56,393
Normal thyroid means no hepatitis.

438
00:24:56,461 --> 00:24:58,261
Could be amyloidosis.

439
00:24:58,329 --> 00:24:59,796
Amyloid buildup hits
the organs, tissue...

440
00:24:59,863 --> 00:25:01,064
her muscles wouldn't have atrophied.

441
00:25:01,132 --> 00:25:02,899
You run the echo on the husband?

442
00:25:02,967 --> 00:25:04,334
Heart's still failing.

443
00:25:04,402 --> 00:25:06,570
The improvement was only temporary.

444
00:25:06,637 --> 00:25:09,772
I prefer the less subtle
answer: you were right, house.

445
00:25:09,840 --> 00:25:14,211
So...less time proving
why hubby isn't dead.

446
00:25:14,278 --> 00:25:18,482
More time proving why kutner is.

447
00:25:18,549 --> 00:25:20,517
Motives for murder.

448
00:25:20,585 --> 00:25:23,120
House...it was a suicide.

449
00:25:23,187 --> 00:25:24,721
The police have already investigated.

450
00:25:24,788 --> 00:25:26,223
They investigated what they saw,

451
00:25:26,290 --> 00:25:27,824
not what they didn't saw.

452
00:25:27,891 --> 00:25:30,960
Talk to friends, classmates,
pizza delivery guy.

453
00:25:31,028 --> 00:25:32,496
And draft foreman.

454
00:25:32,563 --> 00:25:33,863
He can make calls through his tears.

455
00:25:33,931 --> 00:25:35,232
No.

456
00:25:35,299 --> 00:25:37,267
Is that no, i'm not
calling my boyfriend,

457
00:25:37,335 --> 00:25:38,468
who apparently called
my boss instead of me

458
00:25:38,536 --> 00:25:39,936
to say he wasn't coming in?

459
00:25:40,004 --> 00:25:41,238
'cause it's really not fair

460
00:25:41,305 --> 00:25:43,039
to have that much
subtext in one syllable.

461
00:25:43,107 --> 00:25:45,275
We all wanna know why kutner did it.

462
00:25:45,343 --> 00:25:49,179
But we're not gonna
waste time chasing ghosts.

463
00:25:50,714 --> 00:25:53,283
You're not remotely curious?

464
00:25:53,351 --> 00:25:55,785
Only why a man who embraces the rational

465
00:25:55,853 --> 00:26:00,923
is suddenly pursuing the irrational.

466
00:26:00,991 --> 00:26:04,127
She could have alpha-1
anti-trypsin deficiency.

467
00:26:04,195 --> 00:26:07,164
Run her aat proteins.

468
00:26:12,303 --> 00:26:14,337
I'd like to be with eddie.

469
00:26:14,405 --> 00:26:16,739
It's too soon after your surgery.

470
00:26:16,807 --> 00:26:19,142
You can ask that someone get your organs

471
00:26:19,210 --> 00:26:20,743
if you die, right?

472
00:26:20,811 --> 00:26:23,780
Even if the donor bank turned them down?

473
00:26:23,847 --> 00:26:26,283
Individual donors can
bypass the registry,

474
00:26:26,350 --> 00:26:29,219
but there are a lot of
other factors...blood type...

475
00:26:29,287 --> 00:26:31,388
i've given him blood.

476
00:26:31,455 --> 00:26:34,324
It's not just... please.

477
00:26:34,392 --> 00:26:41,198
If i go before him, i want
you to give him my heart.

478
00:26:41,265 --> 00:26:44,033
This isn't over yet.

479
00:26:44,101 --> 00:26:49,673
For me. But it is for him, isn't it?

480
00:26:49,740 --> 00:26:51,941
Yes.

481
00:26:55,313 --> 00:26:57,681
Remy hadley. I also answer to thirteen.

482
00:26:57,748 --> 00:27:00,083
I sometimes sleep with you.

483
00:27:00,150 --> 00:27:02,085
I know i should have called.

484
00:27:02,152 --> 00:27:04,921
I just need some time.

485
00:27:04,988 --> 00:27:08,157
Alone?

486
00:27:08,226 --> 00:27:11,194
I've worked through a lot
of bad stuff in my life.

487
00:27:11,262 --> 00:27:14,931
Always done it solo.

488
00:27:20,438 --> 00:27:24,006
So i should go.

489
00:27:24,074 --> 00:27:27,544
I'm sorry.

490
00:27:27,612 --> 00:27:30,247
Okay.

491
00:27:41,191 --> 00:27:44,794
I.t.'s been trying to close
out kutner's email account.

492
00:27:44,862 --> 00:27:47,764
Apparently, someone's
still logged onto it.

493
00:27:47,831 --> 00:27:51,434
It wasn't hard to figure out
that his password was kutner.

494
00:27:51,502 --> 00:27:53,136
He did what they tell you not to.

495
00:27:53,203 --> 00:27:55,305
He wasn't murdered.
But his parents were.

496
00:27:55,373 --> 00:27:57,507
And the guy who killed them
is coming up for parole.

497
00:27:57,575 --> 00:28:00,176
He's coming up for parole.
He's not out on parole.

498
00:28:00,244 --> 00:28:03,713
Kutner testified at
every one of his hearings.

499
00:28:03,781 --> 00:28:06,249
The guy wouldn't be the first
to see the clock ticking.

500
00:28:06,317 --> 00:28:08,285
He was killed by his own gun.

501
00:28:08,352 --> 00:28:10,920
Which he bought years ago,
obviously for self-defense.

502
00:28:10,988 --> 00:28:13,055
In the temple. Cops found residue.

503
00:28:13,123 --> 00:28:14,957
Right, the murderer would never try to

504
00:28:15,025 --> 00:28:18,928
make it look like suicide...
that would be unethical.

505
00:28:22,266 --> 00:28:24,334
You haven't asked about my patient.

506
00:28:24,402 --> 00:28:26,670
You're waiting on aat protein results.

507
00:28:26,737 --> 00:28:28,838
Means you checked up to
see that i'm still on it.

508
00:28:28,906 --> 00:28:32,776
You wanna transfer the case,
but you won't because you think

509
00:28:32,843 --> 00:28:35,345
it's the only thing
that's holding me together.

510
00:28:35,413 --> 00:28:38,281
Relax. Either i'm right or i'm wrong.

511
00:28:38,349 --> 00:28:39,982
We'll know soon enough.

512
00:28:40,050 --> 00:28:42,552
Find what's killing your patient...

513
00:28:42,620 --> 00:28:45,789
and then i'll find you another patient.

514
00:28:50,562 --> 00:28:51,896
What happened? Nurses
found her like this.

515
00:28:51,963 --> 00:28:53,163
She broke into the cart

516
00:28:53,231 --> 00:28:55,032
and injected whatever she could grab.

517
00:28:55,099 --> 00:28:56,500
Dumb way to look worse for eddie.

518
00:28:56,568 --> 00:28:59,336
She wasn't trying to look worse.

519
00:28:59,404 --> 00:29:02,006
She was trying to kill herself.

520
00:29:04,016 --> 00:29:05,517
she's stable,

521
00:29:05,584 --> 00:29:08,453
but whatever was left of her
liver is definitely shot now.

522
00:29:08,521 --> 00:29:10,087
And there's no change in eddie.

