one, mistook for cancer.

609
00:33:31,115 --> 00:33:33,149
It's very rare, very curable.

610
00:33:33,217 --> 00:33:35,118
I'm starting you on itraconazole.

611
00:33:35,186 --> 00:33:37,520
But how come i was getting
better without the medicine?

612
00:33:37,588 --> 00:33:40,123
Your emotional state
bumped your catecholamines

613
00:33:40,191 --> 00:33:41,657
which helped raise your prolactin.

614
00:33:41,726 --> 00:33:42,792
My emotional state?

615
00:33:42,860 --> 00:33:44,527
Three months of treatment,

616
00:33:44,595 --> 00:33:47,663
you'll be back to your
buff, chiseled self.

617
00:33:47,732 --> 00:33:51,134
I don't want the treatment.

618
00:33:51,202 --> 00:33:53,236
Do the transplant.

619
00:33:53,303 --> 00:33:56,072
But you'd be trading...

620
00:33:56,140 --> 00:33:58,908
the certainty that you'll live

621
00:33:58,976 --> 00:34:00,777
for the uncertainty that she'll live.

622
00:34:00,845 --> 00:34:03,579
I was ready to die anyway.

623
00:34:03,647 --> 00:34:07,617
Now you get to be
nicer to your next wife.

624
00:34:10,755 --> 00:34:13,422
If you won't do it... release me.

625
00:34:13,490 --> 00:34:16,692
And when i get hit by a car

626
00:34:16,761 --> 00:34:20,730
and show up in your morgue,

627
00:34:20,798 --> 00:34:24,700
you can give her my liver then.

628
00:34:27,911 --> 00:34:29,813
you're basically asking
us to commit murder.

629
00:34:29,880 --> 00:34:31,414
I was yesterday too.

630
00:34:31,482 --> 00:34:33,683
There's a difference when
he has 20 years to live

631
00:34:33,751 --> 00:34:35,284
instead of two days.

632
00:34:35,353 --> 00:34:36,919
Not really. Not legally.

633
00:34:36,987 --> 00:34:38,955
That's your way of
convincing us to do this,

634
00:34:39,022 --> 00:34:40,724
by saying it's no more immoral?

635
00:34:40,791 --> 00:34:42,759
The idiot is gonna do
this with or without us.

636
00:34:42,827 --> 00:34:44,361
This way we can protect the organ.

637
00:34:44,428 --> 00:34:46,028
We should be protecting him.

638
00:34:46,096 --> 00:34:49,031
So we strap him to the bed,
wait till his wife dies?

639
00:34:49,099 --> 00:34:52,101
I'm not doing this.

640
00:34:55,473 --> 00:34:58,842
I will.

641
00:34:58,909 --> 00:35:02,645
We've already had one pointless death.

642
00:35:06,283 --> 00:35:09,586
Eddie...what's going on?

643
00:35:09,653 --> 00:35:13,356
I don't know. He just came and got me.

644
00:35:13,424 --> 00:35:15,892
Your husband has a curable disease,

645
00:35:15,959 --> 00:35:18,194
but he wants to die so
he can give you his liver.

646
00:35:18,262 --> 00:35:19,529
Are you okay with that,

647
00:35:19,597 --> 00:35:21,197
or would you rather
he take the treatment?

648
00:35:21,265 --> 00:35:23,433
You son of a bitch! Eddie, don't!

649
